      • vanillaInsertion

        public static int vanillaInsertion(Block target,
                   ItemStack source,
                   int amount,
                   BlockFace side,
                   boolean sorting,
                   UUID inserterId)
        Attempt to insert items from the given buffer into the given block, which should be a vanilla inventory holder. Items successfully inserted will be removed from the buffer stack.
        Parameters:
        target - the block to insert into
        source - the item stack to take items from
        amount - the number of items from the buffer to insert
        side - the side on which insertion is occurring (some blocks care about this, e.g. furnace)
        inserterId - UUID of the player doing the insertion (may be null or the UUID of an offline player)
        Returns:
        the number of items actually inserted

                          int amount,
                          ItemStack buffer,
                          Filter filter,
                          UUID pullerId)
        Attempt to pull items from an inventory into a receiving buffer.
        Parameters:
        target - the block containing the target inventory
        amount - the desired number of items
        buffer - an item stack into which to insert the transferred items
        filter - a filter to whitelist/blacklist items
        pullerId - UUID of the player doing the pulling (may be null or the UUID of an offline player)
        Returns:
        the items pulled, or null if nothing was pulled
